<subSubSection id="C36696BB8E59FFB4FF1AFCD6DB2FFC30" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3C5308E59FFB4FF1AFCD6DB2FFC30" blockId="2.[163,1070,813,982]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Comment 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FEF6FCD6DB70FCA4" baseAuthorityName="BERNHAUER &amp; SCHEERPELTZ" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[335,525,813,834]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FEF6FCD6DB70FCA4" box="[335,525,813,834]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Brachida africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E59FFB4FCE1FCD6DAC8FCA5" box="[856,949,813,835]" name="Tanzania" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and subsequently reported also from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E59FFB4FE70FCB0DB76FC86" box="[457,523,843,864]" name="Kenya" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FDA7FCB1DBE8FC86" author="PACE R" box="[542,661,842,864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="117 - 193" refId="ref7719" refString="PACE R. (1994): Aleocharinae della sottoregione africana orientale al Museo di Ginevra (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) Parte I. - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 100 (4): 117 - 193." type="journal article" year="1994">PACE 1994</bibRefCitation>
). The aedeagus of the above males is practically identical to the drawing of the aedagus of one of the 
<typeStatus id="54C77B928E59FFB4FC88FC93DA20FC9B" box="[817,861,872,893]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">type</typeStatus>
specimens provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FF7DFC7DD83AFC7D" author="PACE R" box="[196,327,901,923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="117 - 193" refId="ref7719" refString="PACE R. (1994): Aleocharinae della sottoregione africana orientale al Museo di Ginevra (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) Parte I. - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 100 (4): 117 - 193." type="journal article" year="1994">PACE (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. The observed slight differences are most likely explained by intraspecific variation. The above specimens represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E59FFB4FCECFC59DAA6FC5E" box="[853,987,930,952]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and the Palaearctic region sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FE27FC3BDB33FC30" author="SMETANA A" box="[414,590,960,982]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref7869" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloeocharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
